        public void onTerminating()
        Description copied from class: AbstractStage
        Event that is triggered, if all of the following conditions hold:
        • while executing the P&F configuration and
        • after receiving the termination signal.

        If stage developers want to override this method, they must always call the super implementation last: 

         @Override
 protected void onTerminating() {
        // insert your code here
        super.onTerminating();
 }

        To throw a checked exception, wrap it to an unchecked exception, e.g. to an IllegalArgumentException.IllegalArgumentException(String, Throwable). Always pass the original exception to the new unchecked exception to allow easy debugging.
